===Awards===
* [[Spanish Cross]] in Bronze (6 June 1939)<ref name="Berger p190"/>
* [[U-boat Front Clasp]] (12 October 1944)<ref name="Berger p190"/>
* [[U-boat War Badge|U-boat War Badge with Diamonds]] (26 January 1943)<ref name="Berger p190"/>
* ''[[Croce di Guerra|Croce di Guerra Italiana al valor militar]]'' (1 November 1941)<ref name="Berger p190"/>
* [[Iron Cross]] (1939)<ref name="Berger p190"/>
** 2nd Class (25 January 1940)
** 1st Class (15 May 1940)
* [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross|Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds]]
** Knight's Cross (24 October 1940) as ''Oberleutnant zur See'' and commander of ''U-138''<ref name="Scherzer p518">Scherzer 2007, p. 518.</ref>
** 142nd Oak Leaves (13 November 1942) as ''Kapit<U+00E4>nleutnant'' and commander of ''U-181''<ref name="Scherzer p518"/>
** 29th Swords (15 April 1943) as ''Kapit<U+00E4>nleutnant'' and commander of ''U-181''<ref name="Scherzer p518"/>
** 7th Diamonds (9 August 1943)  as ''Korvettenkapit<U+00E4>n'' and commander of ''U-181''<ref name="Scherzer p518"/>
* Mentioned twice in the [[Wehrmachtbericht]]

===References in the Wehrmachtbericht===
{|class="wikitable"
! Date
! Original German Wehrmachtbericht wording
! Direct English translation
|-
| Monday, 23&nbsp;September&nbsp;1940 || ''An den im Wehrmachtbericht vom 21. September gemeldeten Unterseebootserfolgen war das unter dem Kommando von Oberleutnant zur See L<U+00FC>th stehende kleine Unterseeboot mit der Versenkung von vier feindlichen Handelsschiffen mit 29&nbsp;000 BRT beteiligt.''<ref >Die Wehrmachtberichte 1939-1945 Band 1, p. 310.</ref> || The small submarine commanded by ''Oberleutnant zur See'' L<U+00FC>th contributed to the submarine successes announced in the ''Wehrmachtbericht'' on 21st September with the sinking of four enemy merchant ships of 29&nbsp;000 GRT.
|-
| Wednesday, 14&nbsp;January&nbsp;1942 || ''Ein Unterseeboot unter F<U+00FC>hrung des Kapit<U+00E4>nleutnants L<U+00FC>th versenkte in z<U+00E4>hen Angriffen aus einem stark gesicherten Geleitzug im Atlantik vier feindlichen Handelsschiffen mit 21&nbsp;000 BRT.''<ref >Die Wehrmachtberichte 1939-1945 Band 2, p. 9.</ref> || A submarine under the leadership of ''Kapit<U+00E4>nleutnant'' L<U+00FC>th sank in tough attacks from a heavily protected convoy four enemy merchant ships of 21&nbsp;000 GRT.
|}

